<TITLE> Dr Wazed's health improving: doctor </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 17 (bdnews24.com)  The health of nuclear scientist Dr Wazed Miah, husband of former prime minister Sheikh Hasina, is improving, his physician said Thursday. "Health condition of Dr Wazed has been improving. He has been recovering. His respiratory problems are almost gone," cardiologist APM Sohrabuzzaman of LabAid Cardiac Hospital said to bdnews24.com. Sohrabuzzaman said Wazed Miah, under treatment at the coronary care unit, would be released in three days. He had been suffering from heart and kidney diseases and high blood pressure and was admitted to the hospital Sunday after he complained of chest pain. He is also a diabetic. bdnews
